 Shawl Escort -- Sunday 3/9/03 at 10:00pm EST</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'll be running the final leg of the Prayer Shawl quest this Sunday for an alt (some of you have grouped with Anda). We'll be forming groups at 1:00pm EST in the Nexus, and porting immediately to Iceclad. Please arrive 15 minutes early to ensure a spot in a group. The raid will be capped at 3 groups.<br>
<br>
Raid Leader:<br>
   Anda Shinycoat (alt of Bartlemeizer)<br>
<br>
Requirements:<br>
   Level 57+<br>
   Positive Thurgadin and Dain faction<br>
<br>
Additional Classes Needed:<br>
All, but especially Tanks, a Shamen <br>
<br>
What this entails:<br>
   A complete description can be found at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/quests/eighth.htm">8th Shawl Quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
   The Thurgadin Prayer Shawl is a set of quests that is designed to build trade-skills as you progress through it. The final step of the 8th shawl is delivering a set of Royal Velium armor to General Bragmur near the bridge in Iceclad, and escorting him across the zone to the Gnome pirates. Along the way, he (and the raiding party) is ambushed by several sets of giants and wolves. <br>
<br>
   The giants must be slain, and General Bragmur must survive in order to complete the quest. In addition to the 8th shawl, several nice items typically drop while killing the wolves/giants along the way.<br>
<br>
    I'll post a couple of hours before the schedule time to confirm that we have enough people to start, and that the trigger spawn (General Bragmur) is up.<br>
<br>
-Bartlemeizer <br>
